## Overview
**Abner W. Berry** (1902 – 1987) was an African American journalist, political activist, and long-time member of the [[Communist Party USA (CPUSA)]]. He was best known for his editorial work with _The Daily Worker_, the official newspaper of the CPUSA, where he focused on issues of racial injustice, labor rights, and socialism. Berry was a vocal advocate for the rights of African Americans and sought to address systemic inequalities through the lens of Marxist ideology.

